<div class="os-eoc os-exercises-container" data-type="composite-page" data-uuid-key=".exercises"><section class="exercises" data-depth="1" id="fs-idm7304032"><h3 data-type="document-title" id="[redacted for uniqueness]"><span class="os-number">7.1</span><span class="os-divider"> </span><span class="os-text">Ionic Bonding</span></h3>
<div class=" os-hasSolution " data-type="exercise" id="fs-idm118463568">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idm84537920"><a class="os-number" href="chapter-7#fs-idm118463568-solution">1</a><span class="os-divider">. </span><div class="os-problem-container">
<p id="fs-idp109455392">Does a cation gain protons to form a positive charge or does it lose electrons?</p>
</div></div>

</div>
<div class=" " data-type="exercise" id="fs-idp12729440">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idm60424368"><span class="os-number">2</span><span class="os-divider">. </span><div class="os-problem-container">
<p id="fs-idm80636720">Iron(III) sulfate [Fe<sub>2</sub>(SO<sub>4</sub>)<sub>3</sub>] is composed of Fe<sup>3+</sup> and <math display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msub><mtext>SO</mtext><mn>4</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mtext>2−</mtext></msup></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msub><mtext>SO</mtext><mn>4</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mtext>2−</mtext></msup></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> ions. Explain why a sample of iron(III) sulfate is uncharged.</p>
</div></div>
</div>
<div class=" os-hasSolution " data-type="exercise" id="fs-idp63165504">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idm95601616"><a class="os-number" href="chapter-7#fs-idp63165504-solution">3</a><span class="os-divider">. </span><div class="os-problem-container">
<p id="fs-idm86462848">Which of the following atoms would be expected to form negative ions in binary ionic compounds and which would be expected to form positive ions: P, I, Mg, Cl, In, Cs, O, Pb, Co?</p>
</div></div>

</div>
<div class=" " data-type="exercise" id="fs-idm89581104">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idm71344160"><span class="os-number">4</span><span class="os-divider">. </span><div class="os-problem-container">
<p id="fs-idm57572832">Which of the following atoms would be expected to form negative ions in binary ionic compounds and which would be expected to form positive ions: Br, Ca, Na, N, F, Al, Sn, S, Cd?</p>
</div></div>
</div>
<div class=" os-hasSolution " data-type="exercise" id="fs-idm94727984">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idm107091360"><a class="os-number" href="chapter-7#fs-idm94727984-solution">5</a><span class="os-divider">. </span><div class="os-problem-container">
