<p id="fs-idm80135200">Methanol, H<sub>3</sub>COH, is used as the fuel in some race cars. Ethanol, C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>5</sub>OH, is used extensively as motor fuel in Brazil. Both methanol and ethanol produce CO<sub>2</sub> and H<sub>2</sub>O when they burn. Write the chemical equations for these combustion reactions using Lewis structures instead of chemical formulas.</p>
